title: For Sale:  Finnish M39
postcontent: Update: 15-Feb-2017: If you've recently contacted me I'm experiencing issues with the e-mail carrier I use for e-mail correspondance.  Basically I'm not able to send or receive emails.  If you could please contact me again through Armslist (I have a different e-mail for Armslist) I would appreciate it.  I'm sorry for the inconvenience.Hello.  For sale is my 1942 Finnish M39 rifle.  These are also referred to as a Finnish Mosin Nagant.  This rifle is chambered in 7.62 x 54r.  This is a VKT manufactured M39 with hex receiver and "D" shank barrel.  The stock has the usual use marks for a WWII battle rifle.  Dents and dings but is in good condition.  There are no cracks that I could find.  For those of you who aren't familiar with this rifle the Fins took captured Mosin Nagant actions and made several improvements over the Russian rifle.  Different barrels (tighter bore to improve accuracy), two stage trigger, better stock (free floated barrel), better sight.  These are very desirable and very accurate rifles.  I purchased this rifle a little over a year ago.  I have put exactly 20 rounds through it.  The rifling is very strong.  This rifle was listed in "Very Good" condition when I purchased it.  The serial numbers on the bolt, receiver, barrel and magazine well are all matching.  The sight has a diefferent number stamped on it.  I couldn't find any other numbers to confirm.  The bluing is more of a pewter color now.  Local sale only please.
